line_1: To recur to whene'er I am tir'd of myself;
line_2: With a bottle or two of prime wine on my shelf,

line_1: Or any thing that but concerns myself,
line_2: May I ne'er heave a sigh for dirty pelf,

line_1: Kept a coach for my sisters, a nag for myself,
line_2: Here I liv'd like a king, never hoarded my pelf,

line_1: I'll live, and be physician to myself.
line_2: For me let GALEN moulder on the shelf,

line_1: To flatter others, or deny myself,
line_2: Me neither pow'r shall tempt, nor thirst of pelf,

line_1: Come, buss me, I'll be Mrs Twitcher myself.
line_2: 'Never hang down your head, you poor penitent elf!

line_1: " That's right, "says Tim," I'll go myself. "
line_2: " Why, fetch him then, you sorry elf; "
